de_portugal is a port of the de_portugal_rc1 map from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.

DE_Portugal is a casual CS:GO map, located in -duh- Portugal, inspired by the typical architecture of small towns/villages. 

It was inspired by Pingo Tinto's original CS:S map, featuring colorful houses, a very unique train station and a church.

My goal with this, was to take what the original map had best and give it a brand new -more CS:GO-ish- look, while still looking typically portuguese. 

The map went through a lot of changes during development since the first version (1 year back), and has been tested several times in a 10v10 environment.

_sText:
de_aerospace is a port of the de_aerospace map from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.

De_Aerospace is a classic bomb-defusal map for Counter Strike: Global Offensive. 

It features a unique two-level linear design that differs from everything else in the main game. 

Dozens of custom models and textures have been made from scratch to solidify the feeling of being on a plane as it travels through the sky. 

Aerospace was developed over a period of around 7-8 months, and has come a long way since then. 

It took several iterations to get the layout functioning, but the final product works quite well! 

We hope you enjoy Aerospace as much as we enjoyed creating it, and have fun!

Welcome to surf_anzchamps, a new and exciting map that is designed to take players on a journey from the ESL Australia Studios all the way through the twists and turns that these shows have to offer!

At tier 2 difficulty this map has been designed for beginners, but don’t stress as some of these stages have been built to challenge even the more experienced surfers. So what are you waiting for? jump in and start exploring the map, as you optimize your routes to set the fastest times!

CS:GO workshop link: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2575133231

Zombies in tunnels, once again! Humans start at the bottom of the map, and have to make their way up the map. Along the way, there are spots for camping, but the map is really good for hunting style of gameplay. You choose what you want to do.

The map is heavily inspired by 4way_tunnels. I never wanted to make an exact copy. So... this is what I came up with. I hope you enjoy. Feel free to leave feedback in the comments. If issues arise, I might be compelled to fix them. It took 3+ months to complete the map.

If you are going to upload the map to a server, please include the .cfg file. It's important!

Biodome - Hostage Rescue
Made by Foofinoo


While a terrorist group has invaded the Black Mesa Research Facility to steal their new energy weapons, something strange seems to have happened in this place...

Most of the inhabitants appear to be missing, as if everyone had suddenly decided to leave overnight. In addition, military equipment and traces of combat are scattered throughout the laboratories. On top of that, strange creatures seem to prowl in these corridors...

Despite all that, the terrorists were still able to get their hands on several scientists. A team of counter-terrorists was sent to rescue them.


After over ten months of development (okay, I did little to nothing for the last two months), here it is: the remake of my own map CS_Biodome!
As always, it has been really fun to build. Perhaps a bit long, but really cool to see the map grow more and more during the first few months.

Yet, I have to admit I was expecting a bit more feedback on the WIP page. At least the few comments were positive...
If you're interested in the map development, you can check that page to find quite a lot of information about it!

As you can see, all the custom content is coming from Black Mesa.
That's right, why not take advantage of the marvellous work from the Crowbar Collective?
Of course, I still had a lot to do to fix, adapt and edit the different assets so that everything fits well in the level.

About the map itself, it is actually a remake of an old map of mine that was originally released for Counter-Strike 1.6 in 2016.
Needless to say, this new version greatly improves the layout, the visuals and more generally every aspect of it.
To put it simply: everything is bigger, larger, greater and in the end (hopefully), better.
I have kept the main ideas I was able to develop on the original map while adding a huge amount of detail and paths as well as some little easter eggs.

Here are a few interesting numbers about the map:
  • A file weight of over 620 MB! (yeah it's quite heavy, but it's because there is a lot of custom stuff, as you will see)
  • About 5830 brushes and 34720 faces!
  • Over 250 custom models!
  • More than 200 custom textures!
  • An estimated making time of: far too much!

Anyway, I really hope you will have fun and enjoy the map!


Foofinoo

Some useful gameplay info:
  • In warden's office CTs can choose between AWPs, armor or tracking prisoners in cells.
  • Green doors are only for CTs, if Ts want to go through them they must destroy them first.
  • In every bottom cell is a toilet with vent, but only 1 or 2 are breakable randomly.
  • Some buttons are only for CTs to prevent early start of a attraction. (4 corners, rope etc.)
  • Crossing the path of a vehicle isn't good idea.

Thanks for download and have fun! :)
